[% META title = 'Ve7tit Theme Fix - September 9, 2025' %]

<h1>Ve7tit Theme Fix - September 9, 2025</h1>

<h2>Issue</h2>
<p>The Ve7tit site was not displaying with the correct theme because it was not mapped in the theme configuration system.</p>

<h2>Root Cause</h2>
<p>The <code>theme_definitions.json</code> file did not include a mapping for the "ve7tit" site name to any theme, causing it to fall back to the default theme instead of the intended APIS (beekeeping) theme.</p>

<h2>Solution</h2>
<p>Added the ve7tit site mapping to the <code>site_themes</code> section in <code>theme_definitions.json</code>:</p>

<pre><code>"site_themes": {
  "ve7tit": "apis",
  // ... other mappings
}</code></pre>

<h2>Files Modified</h2>
<ul>
<li><code>Comserv/root/static/config/theme_definitions.json</code> - Added ve7tit → apis mapping</li>
</ul>

<h2>Testing</h2>
<ul>
<li>Verified that Ve7tit site now correctly loads with the APIS theme</li>
<li>Confirmed honeycomb background and yellow/orange color scheme are applied</li>
<li>All existing site themes remain functional</li>
</ul>

<h2>Todo System Integration</h2>
<ul>
<li>Created todo item (ID: 181) to track this fix</li>
<li>Marked as completed after successful implementation</li>
<li>Added to development workflow for future theme mapping issues</li>
</ul>

<h2>Impact</h2>
<ul>
<li>Ve7tit site now displays with proper beekeeping-themed styling</li>
<li>Consistent user experience across all beekeeping-related sites</li>
<li>Improved theme system reliability</li>
</ul>

